e New York Times", "subsection_name": null, "lead_paragraph": "At 97, Lawrence Ferlinghetti is finally finishing a book about his life, to the great delight of his longtime agent, Sterling Lord, 95.", "pub_date": "2016-06-26T00:00:00Z", "news_desk": "Styles", "headline": {"print_headline": "A Beat Generation Bromance", "main": "A Literary Bromance, Now in Its Sixth Decade"}, "print_page": "1", "snippet": "At 97, Lawrence Ferlinghetti is finally finishing a book about his life, to the great delight of his longtime agent, Sterling Lord, 95.", "_id": "576e563838f0d87405ee5fc7", "slideshow_credits": null, "abstract": "Famed American poet Lawrence Ferlinghetti, at age 97, is writing his first novel, entitled To the Light House, which comes as happy surprise to his longtime literary agent Sterling Lord, who is shopping it around; Ferlinghetti and Lord, two towering legends in publishing world, have known each other since 1950s and are last living links to Beat Generation."}